<item>
            <title>[HBASE-6441] MasterFS doesn&apos;t set scheme for internal FileSystem</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6441</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FSUtils.getRootDir() just takes a configuration object, which is used to:&lt;br/&gt;
1) Get the name of the root directory&lt;br/&gt;
2) Create a filesystem (based on the configured scheme)&lt;br/&gt;
3) Qualify the root onto the filesystem&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the FileSystem from the master filesystem won&apos;t generate the correctly qualified root directory under hadoop-2.0 (though it works fine on hadoop-1.0). Seems to be an issue with the configuration parameters.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
